# 🔒 NEVER commit secrets

Full policy: see `AGENTS.md`.

Never stage/commit/push real passwords, API keys, OAuth client secrets (`GOCSPX-…`),
Google API keys (`AIza…`), AWS keys (`AKIA…`), JWT secrets, or payment keys.

Real values live only in gitignored files (`src/main/resources/application-local.yaml`,
`.env`, `.env.production`) or environment variables. Only `*.example` templates with
placeholders are committed.

Before committing: review `git diff --staged` for secrets; never `git add -A` blindly;
never remove `.gitignore` entries that protect secret files.
